        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 4:49AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 448 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Bryson City, or 5 miles southeast of Smoky
Mountains-Fontana Area, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fontana Lake, Smoky Mountains-Deep Creek, Luada, Stecoah, and
Almond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
